{"name": "beku-stackabletech", "metadata": {"name": "beku-stackabletech", "version": "0.0.10", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["Jinja2", "PyYAML"], "summary": "Test suite expander for Stackable Kuttl tests.", "upload_time": 1730898195}, "documentation": ["# beku\n\nVersion: 0.0.10\n\nFast [Kuttl](https://kuttl.dev/) tests expander for Stackable integration tests.\n\n```sh\nbeku -i tests/test-definition.yaml -t tests/templates/kuttl -k tests/kuttl-test.yaml.jinja2 -o tests/_work\n```\n\n`beku` parses a test definition YAML file together with a directory of templated Kuttl test definitions.\nFrom this it generates Kuttl test suites which can then be run with plain Kuttl.\nThis was built on top of Kuttl to support running tests with different version combinations of products, or slightly different features enabled,\nwithout having to duplicate tests.\n\n## Installation\n\nWe recommend to use [pipx](https://pypa.github.io/pipx/):\n\n```sh\npipx install beku-stackabletech\n```\n\nBut you can also use `pip`:\n\n```sh\n# from PyPI\npip install beku-stackabletech\n# from GitHub\npip install git+https://github.com/stackabletech/beku.py.git@main\n```\n\nOr via NixOS and Nix Shell:\n\n```nix\n{ lib, pkgs, ... }:\nwith lib;\nlet\n  beku = pkgs.callPackage(pkgs.fetchFromGitHub {\n    owner = \"stackabletech\";\n    repo = \"beku.py\";\n    rev = \"145e8210f5786b8128e3af43f60b61f065cc2c39\";\n    hash = \"sha256-hLaIY4BE+VIMeKmS3JLOZy87OC2VuQtbX/NCIbQr2p4=\"; # use lib.fakeHash to find new hashes when upgrading\n  } + \"/beku.nix\") {};\nin\n{\n  packages = with pkgs; [\n    beku\n    # ...\n  ];\n\n  // ...\n}\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```sh\ncd <stackable operator directory>\nrm -rf tests/_work && beku\ncd tests/_work && kubectl kuttl test\n```\n\nAlso see the `examples` folder.\n\n## Release a new version\n\nUpdate the version in:\n\n* `src/beku/version.py`\n* `README.md` : version and pip install command.\n\nUpdate the CHANGELOG.\nCommit and tag.\nBuild and publish:\n\n```sh\nrm -rf dist/\npython -m build --sdist --wheel .\ntwine upload dist/*\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "beku.test", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream.test_default_test_suite", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream.test_patch_implicit_select", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream.test_patch_ignores_test_that_was_not_selected", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream.test_patch_the_same_dimension_twice", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream.test_patch_the_same_test_twice", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream.test_patch_str_expression", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream.test_resolve_explicit_select", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream.test_resolve_select_all", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "beku.test.test_render_from_stream.TestRenderFromStream.test_multiple_patches", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "beku.main", "documentation": ["Main entry point."], "functions": [{"name": "beku.main.parse_cli_args", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "Namespace", "xref": {"fqname": "argparse.Namespace", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Parse command line args."]}, {"name": "beku.main._cli_log_level", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cli_arg", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "beku.main.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Main"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "beku", "documentation": ["Test suite expander for Kuttl tests."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "beku.version", "documentation": ["Package version."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "beku.version.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "beku.__main__", "documentation": ["Package entry point."], "functions":